info.headline: Flood Warning issued March 29 at 7:32AM CDT by NWS Green Bay WI
info.description:
...The National Weather Service in Green Bay has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin...
Wisconsin River below Wausau affecting Marathon County.
* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring.
* WHERE...Wisconsin River below Wausau.
* WHEN...From this morning until further notice.
* IMPACTS...At 1167.0 feet, Water approaches buildings in DC Everest Park and Oak Island Park.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:10 AM CDT Saturday the stage was 1167.8 feet and rising. - Bankfull stage is 1065.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 7:10 AM CDT Saturday was 1167.8 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 1167.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas.
Please report observed flooding to local emergency services or law enforcement and request they pass this information to the National Weather Service when you can do so safely.
Additional information is available at www.weather.gov/grb
The next statement will be issued this evening by 1100 PM CDT.

parameter.value: FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS MORNING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE
